communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

On April 7, 2023, the Seattle Times reported "Port of Seattle nearly lost $570K to phishing emails, prompting audit" (https://www.seattletimes.com/seattle-news/port-of-seattle-nearly-lost-570k-to-phishing-emails-prompting-audit/).

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request copies of the phishing emails, both as originally received and as forwarded to the Port's accounts payable department.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Kevin Wallace

title: Right to Repair Correspondence (New York State Assembly)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

- Emails, text messages, phone call logs, virtual conferencing logs, visitor and appointment logs since 2014 containing one or more of the following non case-sensitive terms "Right to Repair", "Repair", "Apple", "Google", "Samsung", "Rossmann", "Louis Rossmann", "Repair Preservation Group", "A6589".

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

UT
